Refactored git-arch to use git rev-parse --parseopt for help handling.

Improved git-arch option parsing by using git's built-in --parseopt feature:
- Replaced manual getopts loop with git rev-parse --parseopt evaluation
- Simplified usage documentation with structured --parseopt format
- Removed manual help and error handling code
- Added proper documentation of options in parseopt format
- Changed variable names from LISTMODE to listmode (lowercase convention)

This makes the script more robust and follows git conventions for argument
parsing. The --parseopt feature handles -h/--help and error messages automatically.

